HUXLEY
Security through Victory, Captain.

DRAGUER
Those were not normal scouts you put us up against, they were elite Karamean attack ships.

HUXLEY
Yes, I know. I had been tracking them for some time before I sent you in to intercept.

DRAGUER
I understand the importance of your research, Doctor, but I would appreciate a heads up next time you put us up against elite forces. 

HUXLEY
I was confident you could handle it. 

DRAGUER
I did, but you are putting my crew in danger.  

HUXLEY
You are a soldier, Captain. Your job is to fight. 

DRAGUER
My crew was trained for the front, not for chasing stray pirates and scouts out here behind the lines. 

HUXLEY
If there is nothing else, Captain, I need to return to my work. 

The Captain is too angry to answer. 

HUXLEY
Security through Victory. 

Huxley hangs up. Drageur is just barely holding it together, but she calms herself down. 

[[Scene: Captain complains to Darsono about the crew]]

CONTROL
